            {
              "type": "title",
              "text": "Reglas Gramaticales",
              "header": true
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "El adjetivo se sitúa casi siempre antes del {SNIPPET}. Con algunos verbos, el adjetivo se coloca después del {SNIPPET}. Estos verbos son: <b><i>to be</b></i> (ser/estar), <b><i>to become</b></i> (ponerse), <b><i>to feel</b></i> (sentirse), <b><i>to look</b></i> (parecer), <b><i>to seem</b></i> (parecer), <b><i>to smell</b></i> (oler), <b><i>to taste</b></i> (gustar).",
              "options": [
                ["sustantivo", "sujeto"],
                ["sujeto", "verbo"]
              ],
              "rightOptions": [0, 1]
            },
            {
              "type": "example",
              "children": [
                {
                  "mainText": "She {SNIPPET} tired.",
                  "subText": "(Parece cansada.)",
                  "options": [
                    ["is", "looks"]
                  ],
                  "rightOptions": [1]
                },
                {
                  "mainText": "I {SNIPPET} good.",
                  "subText": "(Me siento bien.)",
                  "options": [
                    ["feel", "look"]
                  ],
                  "rightOptions": [0]
                },
                {
                  "mainText": "It {SNIPPET} bad.",
                  "subText": "(Huele mal.)",
                  "options": [
                    ["tastes", "smells"]
                  ],
                  "rightOptions": [1]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Los adjetivos en inglés <b><i>no</b></i> tiene <u>género</u>."
            },
            {
              "type": "example",
              "children": [
                {
                  "mainText": "She {SNIPPET} tired.",
                  "subText": "(Parece cansada.)",
                  "options": [
                    ["is", "looks"]
                  ],
                  "rightOptions": [1]
                },
                {
                  "mainText": "the car is {SNIPPET}.",
